  "prompt": "Is yahoo near half as successful as Google?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Google and Yahoo operate at very different scales and levels of success. \n\nGoogle, owned by Alphabet Inc., has become a dominant force in numerous sectors including search engines, advertising technology, cloud computing, artificial intelligence, and more. Google's search engine has a significant market share, often reported to be around 90% globally. Additionally, other ventures like YouTube, Google Maps, Google Drive, and Android OS contribute to its widespread success and revenue generation.\n\nYahoo, now owned by Apollo Global Management, has a much smaller footprint in comparison. Although Yahoo continues to operate in certain areas such as news, finance, and email services, it does not command nearly the same market share or revenue as Google. Yahoo's search engine market share is vastly overshadowed by Google.\n\nIn terms of financial success, user base, and technological innovation, Google is substantially more successful than Yahoo. It would be inaccurate to say that Yahoo is near half as successful as Google, as the gap between the two companies is quite large.",
